Quarkdown documents support emojis either by direct insertion or through a shortcode.

### Direct insertion

You can directly insert emoji characters into your source code:

```markdown
Quarkdown's logo is not a planet ğŸª
I love Quarkdown! ğŸ˜
```

### Shortcode function

You can use the `.emoji`<sup>[[docs]](https://quarkdown.com/docs/quarkdown-stdlib/com.quarkdown.stdlib.module.Emoji/emoji.html)</sup> function with a shortcode:

```
Quarkdown's logo is not a planet .emoji {ringed-planet}
I love Quarkdown! .emoji {heart-eyes}
```

> [!NOTE]
> During compilation, the first call to `.emoji` in a document will load the entire emoji set, which may slightly increase compilation time.
> Subsequent calls will be faster.

For a complete list of supported shortcodes, refer to the [Emoji Cheat Sheet](https://quarkdown.com/docs/emoji-list/).

